      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T20:57:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are we supposed to accept more than one value here? It seems odd to me that for auth we\u0027re saying \"if any of your tokens match, you\u0027re authorized\".",
      "revId": "70925b7ad845c6162e47854cdb808571e02cbf5e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "af4a4f91_4e2f1784",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/common.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 243,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T01:40:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally speaking, there is no guarantee that the header key is exclusively used by this module only. A request could be parsed through multiple layers, and each could have put a token with the header key for own use.\n\nOf course, we don\u0027t have such a case. I removed the loop to use the first value. (Why not the last one? it\u0027s a random pick.)",
      "parentUuid": "7019595f_6168db45",
      "revId": "70925b7ad845c6162e47854cdb808571e02cbf5e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "167985e2_00e05d63",
        "filename": "buildbucket/appengine/rpc/common.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 244,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T20:09:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Strictly speaking this should use https://golang.org/pkg/crypto/subtle/#ConstantTimeCompare otherwise it is possible to \"guess\" the token by measuring how fast request fails (it will require a lot of trials though).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 244,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 244,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "70925b7ad845c6162e47854cdb808571e02cbf5e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
